SCOTT CLELAND: And let me be
very clear.

20:27.760 --> 20:33.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think ISPs would be more than
happy if there
was congressional legislation
that applied

20:33.432 --> 20:38.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the same rules to everybody,
technology-neutral,
and put the consumer truly in
control.

20:39.004 --> 20:41.807 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We agree the consumer should be
put in control.

20:41.841 --> 20:44.543 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think they'd have some great
support of
that.

20:44.577 --> 20:47.680 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
However, I don't think you would
have Google,
Facebook and Amazon and those,
they would

20:47.713 --> 20:48.914 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
say no way.

20:48.948 --> 20:51.784 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GIGI SOHN: William, the answer
is much simpler
than that.

20:51.817 --> 20:55.121 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Federal Communications
Commission regulates
networks.

20:55.154 --> 20:58.891 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It doesn't regulate Amazon,
Google and Facebook.

20:58.924 --> 21:00.860 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It doesn't have the legal power.

21:00.893 --> 21:05.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If we had gone ahead and done
that -- and
it was interesting to see our
Republican colleagues

21:05.865 --> 21:09.401 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
urging us to do that, when they
know full
well we don't have the power.

21:09.435 --> 21:13.072 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If we had done that, it would
have been thrown
out in court.

21:13.105 --> 21:14.573 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So we couldn't do that.

21:14.607 --> 21:16.308 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But here's what's interesting.

21:16.342 --> 21:19.078 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Google opposed these rules.

21:19.111 --> 21:20.813 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Why?

21:20.846 --> 21:23.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Not because it would have
applied to them,
but because they knew that this
served as

21:23.516 --> 21:25.017 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a template.

21:25.050 --> 21:29.155 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
These rules serve as a template
that Congress
could use to raise the bar.

21:29.188 --> 21:31.557 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But, instead, the bar has been
eliminated.

21:31.590 --> 21:37.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: So, right now,
though, if
I'm a consumer and these rules
are now moot,

21:37.296 --> 21:41.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and I want to protect my
privacy, like, what
can I ask of my ISP?

21:41.066 --> 21:45.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What are they allowed to do as
far as collecting
information about me, selling
information

21:45.771 --> 21:47.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
about me right now?

21:47.573 --> 21:53.078 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GIGI SOHN: After all the
blowback, when the
Senate and the House passed this
law repealing

21:53.112 --> 21:55.714 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the FCC's rules, there was huge
amounts of
blowback.

21:55.748 --> 21:57.816 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't think anybody expected
it.

21:57.850 --> 22:05.291 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, Comcast, AT&amp;T and I believe
Verizon all
posted blog posts saying that,
you know, we

22:05.324 --> 22:07.326 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
don't use this information.

22:07.359 --> 22:09.328 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We don't share this information.

22:09.361 --> 22:11.430 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have no plans to do so.

22:11.463 --> 22:13.199 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We don't currently do so.

22:13.232 --> 22:15.034 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: You don't buy
it?

22:15.067 --> 22:18.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GIGI SOHN: Well, no, I buy it
that today,
they do not, but they want the
leave the door

22:18.837 --> 22:24.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
open to selling and sharing the
most sensitive
personal information, your
health care information,

22:24.810 --> 22:29.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
your financial information, your
location,
your Social Security number.

22:29.982 --> 22:32.084 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They want to leave that door
open.

22:32.117 --> 22:36.889 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT CLELAND: It's very
important, if I can
correct, they're saying health
care information,

22:36.922 --> 22:38.591 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
financial information.

22:38.624 --> 22:42.261 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's part of the patchwork of
privacy regulations.

22:42.294 --> 22:45.564 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Those -- all right, that's
sensitive data.

22:45.598 --> 22:48.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Companies like an ISP or even
Google shouldn't
be sharing that stuff.

22:48.968 --> 22:50.769 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's a big no-no.

22:50.803 --> 22:55.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when we talk about trying to
scare people
about this, financial
information and health

22:55.474 --> 22:57.610 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
care information is covered
under other laws.

22:57.643 --> 23:01.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All right,
Scott Cleland,
Gigi Sohn, thank you both very
much.

23:02.014 --> 23:06.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GIGI SOHN: Thank you.

23:06.085 --> 23:10.122 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SCOTT CLELAND: Thank you.

23:10.155 --> 23:15.194 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

23:15.227 --> 23:21.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
advertisers distance
themselves from FOX News amid
sexual harassment

23:21.567 --> 23:27.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
allegations; why Texas puts
cameras in many
of its classrooms; and an
acclaimed author

23:27.873 --> 23:31.677 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
gives the advice he wishes he
had known as
a young writer.

23:31.710 --> 23:38.050 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But first: Jordan's King
Abdullah will meet
with President Trump tomorrow
here in Washington.

23:38.083 --> 23:42.087 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One item on the agenda: the
growth of Jewish
settlements on the West Bank.

23:42.121 --> 23:48.727 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
More than half-a-million
Israelis live there
on land captured from Jordan 50
years ago,

23:48.761 --> 23:53.332 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
land that many Israelis claim as
a biblical
birthright, but that
Palestinians hope will

23:53.365 --> 23:55.634 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
comprise a future state.

23:55.668 --> 23:59.672 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
From the West Bank, special
correspondent
Martin Seemungal reports.

23:59.705 --> 24:05.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: Israeli
soldiers and police
mobilizing in the West Bank to
arrest and

24:05.411 --> 24:13.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
remove Israelis, by force if
necessary, a
settler outpost at Amona judged
by Israeli

24:13.385 --> 24:18.691 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
courts to be illegal because it
is built on
land owned by Palestinians.

24:18.724 --> 24:23.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The West Bank was captured by
Israel during
the 1967 war.

24:23.462 --> 24:26.799 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
International law considers it
occupied territory.

24:26.832 --> 24:31.503 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Israel disputes this and has
been building
Jewish settlements for decades.

24:31.537 --> 24:33.272 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Amona is different.

24:33.305 --> 24:37.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's one of the settlements
built without
Israeli government authorization
on private

24:37.476 --> 24:39.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Palestinian land.

24:39.244 --> 24:44.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
No government wants to use
troops against
its own citizens, especially
Prime Minister

24:44.883 --> 24:47.720 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Benjamin Netanyahu's right-wing
coalition.

24:47.753 --> 24:53.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, as the protesting settlers
were taken
away, he announced plans for a
major settlement

24:53.425 --> 24:57.062 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
expansion in another area of the
West Bank.

24:57.096 --> 25:02.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Netanyahu also promised to build
a new settlement
for the Jews evicted from Amona.

25:02.101 --> 25:07.873 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He delivered on that promise,
announcing plans
for the first completely new
settlement in

25:07.906 --> 25:09.808 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
over 20 years.

25:09.842 --> 25:16.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It will be built in the Shilo
area, near Nablus,
a powerful message in support of
these settlers

25:16.715 --> 25:20.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and one of their beliefs that
God gave these
lands to the Jews.

25:20.119 --> 25:25.457 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HAGAI BEN ARTZI, Beit El
Resident: We're standing
on this site of the dream of
Jacob.

25:25.491 --> 25:30.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: Not far from
Amona, Hagai
Ben Artzi points to ruins that
he says mark

25:30.429 --> 25:36.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the biblical site of Jacob's
Ladder, the dream
where God promised the land of
Israel to the

25:36.101 --> 25:38.003 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Jewish people in the Book of
Genesis.

25:38.036 --> 25:45.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HAGAI BEN ARTZI: The roots of
the people of
Israel are in this place, and
the whole Zionist

25:45.444 --> 25:52.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
idea is the return of the Jewish
people to
the biblical land, to its
biblical homeland.

25:52.785 --> 25:57.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: Ben Artzi is
the brother-in-law
of Prime Minister Netanyahu, and
a prominent

25:57.222 --> 26:02.761 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
citizen of Beit El, one of
nearly 200 settlements
across the West Bank.

26:02.795 --> 26:05.697 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He has lived here for 40 years.

26:05.731 --> 26:10.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Like many settlements, Beit El
started out
as a few caravans on a hilltop.

26:10.402 --> 26:13.605 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Osnat Sharon is one of the
original settlers.

26:13.639 --> 26:16.975 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She calls this area by its
biblical names,
Judea and Samaria.

26:17.009 --> 26:22.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
OSNAT SHARON, Beit El Resident:
I felt like
a pioneer, to build a new place
in an empty

26:22.748 --> 26:25.451 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
place, and there was nothing
here, nothing.

26:25.484 --> 26:30.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: Palestinians
argue that
the whole settlement is illegal
because of

26:30.055 --> 26:35.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
international law, and that at
least part
of Beit El was built on private
land, farmland

26:35.461 --> 26:38.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that they say they haven't been
able to use
for years.

26:38.664 --> 26:44.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The issue is still in court and
that section
of Beit El remains off-limits to
building.

26:45.003 --> 26:50.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The rest of Beit El has boomed
since those
early days, nearly 7,000 people
today, permanent

26:50.676 --> 26:55.347 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
buildings, a supermarket,
playgrounds, like
any small town.

26:55.380 --> 26:59.818 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They come from Israel, from
different countries,
many from the U.S.

26:59.852 --> 27:05.023 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One study estimates 15 percent
of the settlers
in the West Bank are American,
and they all

27:05.057 --> 27:09.962 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
believe that it is their right
to be here.

27:09.995 --> 27:15.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Less than a mile from the
playgrounds of Beit
El, Palestinian children are at
recess at

27:15.033 --> 27:16.768 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a Ramallah school.

27:16.802 --> 27:22.307 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Ramallah is the seat of
government for the
Palestinian Authority, and under
its control.

27:22.341 --> 27:27.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Israeli soldiers control access
points to
the city, and Palestinians say
soldiers routinely

27:27.479 --> 27:30.782 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
conduct raids, often in the
middle of the
night.

27:30.816 --> 27:33.986 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Access to farmland is severely
restricted.

27:34.019 --> 27:37.756 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The job market here is limited.

27:37.789 --> 27:41.693 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Settlements like Beit El are
built on land
the Palestinians hope will be
part of their

27:41.727 --> 27:43.495 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
future state.

27:43.529 --> 27:47.332 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The settlements are often a
focal point of
Palestinian anger, leading to
clashes with

27:47.366 --> 27:52.437 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
settlers and Israeli soldiers
who control
the lands where the settlements
are built.

27:52.471 --> 27:57.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hard-line Palestinians still
believe all of
the West Bank and Israel is
occupied land

27:57.543 --> 27:59.378 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that belongs to them.

27:59.411 --> 28:04.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There has been relative calm in
the West Bank
in recent months, the result of
ongoing security

28:04.116 --> 28:08.787 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
cooperation between the
Palestinian Authority
and Israel.

28:08.820 --> 28:14.192 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Husam Zomlot is a senior adviser
to Palestinian
Leader Mahmoud Abbas.

28:14.226 --> 28:17.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He says using violence against
Jewish settlers
is counterproductive.

28:17.462 --> 28:20.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HUSAM ZOMLOT, Palestinian
Presidential Adviser:
We don't hate them.

28:20.232 --> 28:26.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In fact, our histories with Jews
have been
an integral part of our national
fabric.

28:26.672 --> 28:34.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What we dislike, however, is
occupiers, colonizers,
the seizures, deniers of our
very basic rights.

28:34.446 --> 28:40.719 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: The tense,
sometimes violent
status quo that has gone on for
decades defined

28:40.752 --> 28:43.689 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
by the enormous security wall
built by Israel.

28:43.722 --> 28:47.059 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It stretches for miles across
the West Bank.

28:47.092 --> 28:51.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Settlers here in Beit El, like
settlers across
the West Bank, have often had a
very complicated

28:51.897 --> 28:57.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
relationship with the United
States, often
perceived as both protector and
enemy at the

28:57.603 --> 28:59.271 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
same time.

28:59.304 --> 29:03.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Obama administration in
particular wasn't
seen as a friend of the
settlers.

29:03.175 --> 29:08.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The arrival of Donald Trump, on
the other
hand, is being welcomed here in
Beit El.

29:08.280 --> 29:10.849 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are hopeful it is the
beginning of a
new era.

29:10.882 --> 29:14.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
Bibi and I have known each other
for a long

29:14.152 --> 29:18.590 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
time, smart man, great
negotiator, and I think
we're going to make a deal.

29:18.624 --> 29:21.093 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: But Netanyahu
made his position
clear.

29:21.126 --> 29:24.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BENJAMIN NETANYAHU, Israeli
Prime Minister:
I believe that the issue of the
settlements

29:24.196 --> 29:28.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is not the core of the conflict,
nor does
it really drive the conflict.

29:28.333 --> 29:33.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: Beit El's new
yeshiva for
Jewish studies is reported to
have White House

29:33.472 --> 29:35.240 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
connections.

29:35.273 --> 29:41.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
David Friedman, Trump's new
ambassador to
Israel, and his son-in-law,
Jared Kushner,

29:41.246 --> 29:43.982 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have donated money to this
yeshiva.

29:44.016 --> 29:49.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Trump has tapped Kushner to lead
negotiations
between Israel and the
Palestinians.

29:49.554 --> 29:53.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The broad parameters of the
so-called two-state
solution would give most of the
West Bank

29:53.592 --> 29:55.994 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to the Palestinians for their
state.

29:56.028 --> 30:00.165 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Israel would keep the major
settlement blocks,
which are close to the 1967
border.

30:00.198 --> 30:04.770 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In exchange, it would give an
equal amount
of land to the Palestinians.

30:04.803 --> 30:09.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it would mean dozens of
settlements like
Beit El would need to be
evacuated.

30:09.541 --> 30:13.578 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
As many as 70,000 Jews live in
these areas.

30:13.612 --> 30:18.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The right-wing Jewish Home
Party, led by Naftali
Bennett, is part of Netanyahu's
coalition.

30:18.850 --> 30:24.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is pushing for unilateral
annexation to
bring all the settlements under
Israeli control.

30:24.923 --> 30:29.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is against the two-state
idea, and it has
pushed through a controversial
law giving

30:29.895 --> 30:36.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Israel the right to build on
private Palestinian
land seen by many as a de facto
form of annexation.

30:36.601 --> 30:41.540 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tzachi Hanegbi is a senior
cabinet minister
with close ties to Netanyahu.

30:41.573 --> 30:45.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Hanegbi insists that the
government remains
committed to the two-state idea.

30:45.777 --> 30:48.747 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He says the Jewish Home Party is
in the minority.

30:48.780 --> 30:52.084 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TZACHI HANEGBI, Israeli Cabinet
Minister:
The majority of Israelis, I
would say an overwhelming

30:52.117 --> 31:00.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
majority, believe that there has
to be a solution,
a peaceful solution, which will
not include

31:00.625 --> 31:02.394 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the annexation.

31:02.427 --> 31:06.331 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: On the Israeli
left, there
are deep worries that continued
construction

31:06.364 --> 31:11.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
