40:30.528 --> 40:33.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's really damaging to
the culture
of a workplace.

40:33.498 --> 40:37.368 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you're saying
that's the
message that's being sent here?

40:37.402 --> 40:40.238 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
NOREEN FARRELL: Without a doubt.

40:40.271 --> 40:46.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Michael Schmidt,
New York Times,
Noreen Farrell, we thank you
very much.

40:46.878 --> 40:55.653 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
NOREEN FARRELL: Thank you.

40:55.687 --> 41:06.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now: a look at
whether having
cameras in the classroom can
protect children

41:06.130 --> 41:12.837 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with disabilities, who can be
targets for
bullying and can be subject to
abuse by teachers.

41:12.870 --> 41:15.506 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But cameras raise their own
issues.

41:15.540 --> 41:20.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Kavitha
Cardoza with
our partner Education Week
traveled to Keller,

41:20.311 --> 41:25.850 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Texas, to see how a
recently-implemented law
is playing out, and all this for
our weekly

41:25.883 --> 41:27.819 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
series Making the Grade.

41:27.852 --> 41:33.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Breggett Rideau
watches her
son Terrence during his weekly
therapy session.

41:33.391 --> 41:38.029 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Horseback riding helps him
improve his balance,
muscle tone and confidence.

41:38.062 --> 41:41.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BREGGETT RIDEAU, Mother of
Terrence Rideau:
I have never seen my son ride on
a horse where

41:41.699 --> 41:43.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
he wasn't smiling.

41:43.201 --> 41:48.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Terrence is 21,
but, developmentally,
he's about 2 or 3.

41:48.039 --> 41:52.110 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BREGGETT RIDEAU: OK, this is a
picture of
little T. when he was just a few
weeks old,

41:52.143 --> 41:53.611 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a few days old.

41:53.644 --> 41:54.645 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He came out smiling.

41:54.679 --> 41:56.114 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

41:56.147 --> 41:58.282 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Breggett says
Terrence was
always a happy little boy.

41:58.316 --> 42:01.185 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Then, in middle school, he
changed.

42:01.219 --> 42:05.990 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BREGGETT RIDEAU: He would cry
out for no reason,
just out -- just cry out, tears.

42:06.023 --> 42:07.959 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I'm like, what's wrong,
babe?

42:07.992 --> 42:09.026 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
A stomach ache.

42:09.060 --> 42:11.062 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I had no idea.

42:11.095 --> 42:15.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: There were
unexplained injuries,
a bump on his head, a broken
thumb, a dislocated

42:15.867 --> 42:17.769 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
knee.

42:17.802 --> 42:22.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Keller School District began
investigating,
and a classroom aide came
forward to substantiate

42:22.106 --> 42:23.574 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
some of Breggett's concerns.

42:23.608 --> 42:25.977 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BREGGETT RIDEAU: Everyone
started telling
me what that teacher had done.

42:26.010 --> 42:29.013 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He had dropped him too many
times to count.

42:29.046 --> 42:32.583 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I found out that he had slammed
little T.
against the wall.

42:32.617 --> 42:34.085 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I had no clue.

42:34.118 --> 42:37.989 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: The Rideaus
were awarded
a $1 million jury settlement.

42:38.022 --> 42:43.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Keller School District is
appealing, and
declined to speak to us for this
story.

42:43.694 --> 42:45.463 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But Breggett wasn't done.

42:45.496 --> 42:50.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
An aspiring jazz singer, she put
her career
on hold and began a campaign to
install cameras

42:50.935 --> 42:53.237 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in special education classrooms.

42:53.271 --> 42:58.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She testified in front of the
Texas House
and Senate, saying cameras would
have prevented

42:58.509 --> 42:59.577 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the abuse.

42:59.610 --> 43:02.480 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BREGGETT RIDEAU: My child
counts.

43:02.513 --> 43:04.415 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Children like mine count, too.

43:04.449 --> 43:07.919 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: In 2015, Texas
agreed.

43:07.952 --> 43:12.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It became the first state in the
country to
require cameras in special
education classrooms,

43:12.857 --> 43:14.158 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
if requested.

43:14.192 --> 43:18.329 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ron Hager is with the National
Disabilities
Rights Network.

43:18.362 --> 43:23.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He says children with
intellectual disabilities
are far more likely to be
abused.

43:23.201 --> 43:25.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RON HAGER, National Disabilities
Rights Network:
Students with disabilities make
up about 12

43:25.503 --> 43:29.140 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
percent of the student
population.

43:29.173 --> 43:32.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have been subjected to
about 70 percent
of the restraints and
seclusions, so it's

43:32.710 --> 43:33.878 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a huge disparity.

43:33.911 --> 43:35.480 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They are very vulnerable.

43:35.513 --> 43:39.817 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Ryder Warren is
the superintendent
of a nearby school district.

43:39.851 --> 43:41.752 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He agrees with the law.

43:41.786 --> 43:42.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYDER WARREN, Superintendent,
Northwest Independent
School District: The mantra of
our school

43:42.487 --> 43:44.388 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
district is, we put kids first.

43:44.422 --> 43:46.657 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
My primary job is to protect
children.

43:46.691 --> 43:50.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, right after that, my job is
to protect
the adults that are in the
buildings, especially

43:50.928 --> 43:52.263 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
our classroom teachers.

43:52.296 --> 43:55.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Under the
current law, teachers
cannot opt out.

43:55.666 --> 43:58.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Neither can parents of other
children with
special needs.

43:58.135 --> 44:00.538 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This could lead to privacy
concerns.

44:00.571 --> 44:06.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYDER WARREN: That's been an
issue with some
parents, that their need for
their kids not

44:06.878 --> 44:09.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be under constant supervision
with that
camera.

44:10.014 --> 44:12.083 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have heard some comments about
that.

44:12.116 --> 44:15.887 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have really not had any
comments from teachers.

44:15.920 --> 44:18.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: The bigger
issue for him
is cost.

44:18.723 --> 44:23.928 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Under the new law, if even one
parent requests
a camera, every special
education classroom

44:23.961 --> 44:26.264 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the entire district has to
have one.

44:26.297 --> 44:30.535 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
RYDER WARREN: That would
probably cost to
the tune of over $600,000.

44:30.568 --> 44:33.137 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That is just an astronomical
time and expense.

44:33.170 --> 44:35.573 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: What would you
say to the
Texas legislature?

44:35.606 --> 44:38.543 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RYDER WARREN: Pay for it.

44:38.576 --> 44:42.914 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Adam Feind is
in charge of
technology for the district.

44:42.947 --> 44:45.082 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The cost of cameras is just the
start.

44:45.116 --> 44:48.786 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ADAM FEIND, Northwest
Independent School District:
A camera such as this costs
about $800.

44:48.819 --> 44:52.423 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
However, when we look at the
total cost of
operation, we have to take into
account the

44:52.456 --> 44:58.195 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
video storage, the wiring, the
cable, the
cost of installing, the cost of
operations.

44:58.229 --> 45:02.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Samantha Crane
is with the
Autistic Self Advocacy Network.

45:02.700 --> 45:04.602 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
She opposes cameras in
classrooms.

45:04.635 --> 45:07.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAMANTHA CRANE, Autistic Self
Advocacy Network:
Parents can't get access to that
footage unless

45:07.672 --> 45:09.440 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
they know something's happened.

45:09.473 --> 45:13.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have to be able to say, I
would like
footage from this day, and
ideally from this

45:13.878 --> 45:15.880 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
particular time of the day.

45:15.913 --> 45:19.817 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, parents might think
everything is fine,
everything's being
tape-recorded, but they're

45:19.850 --> 45:23.254 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
still not getting the
information they need
to know, if their child is safe.

45:23.287 --> 45:27.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Crane worries
abuse may go
underground, and take resources
away from

45:27.992 --> 45:29.860 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
education.

45:29.894 --> 45:33.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Instead, several disability
advocacy groups
say they would rather see more
special education

45:34.031 --> 45:39.870 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
students in mainstream
classrooms, more teacher
training, and more background
checks for staff.

45:39.904 --> 45:43.007 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It isn't clear whether cameras
will actually
protect students.

45:43.040 --> 45:47.478 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
A lot depends on how the
technology is implemented
and monitored.

45:47.511 --> 45:52.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For example, last year, after
the cameras
were installed in Terrence's
classroom, Breggett

45:52.683 --> 45:58.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rideau noticed her son came home
looking troubled,
so she asked to review the
footage.

45:58.789 --> 46:03.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Terrence starts choking, and
then eight minutes
of the tape is missing.

46:03.094 --> 46:07.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Breggett believes the tape was
manipulated,
and is urging for systems that
would protect

46:07.498 --> 46:08.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the footage.

46:08.866 --> 46:12.603 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Still, she believes cameras are
the best way
to protect children.

46:12.637 --> 46:16.474 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BREGGETT RIDEAU: Because it's
the only voice
for a child that can't talk.

46:16.507 --> 46:19.176 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's, like, that simple.

46:19.210 --> 46:22.380 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: She spends her
time helping
other parents advocate.

46:22.413 --> 46:28.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BREGGETT RIDEAU: My phone was
blowing up from
Canada from Canada to Florida to
North Carolina.

46:28.552 --> 46:30.655 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We all have a child that's
vulnerable.

46:30.688 --> 46:35.960 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Breggett has
gone back to
work part-time, but takes her
fight for her

46:35.993 --> 46:37.928 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
son's safety along with her.

46:37.962 --> 46:40.531 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BREGGETT RIDEAU: I have a
special-needs son
who was hurt at school.

46:40.564 --> 46:41.799 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It almost killed me, but I'm
still here.

46:41.832 --> 46:43.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, this song right here I hope
explains how
I feel about it.

46:43.200 --> 46:44.201 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: The title?

46:44.235 --> 46:46.070 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
"Here's to Life."

46:46.103 --> 46:58.683 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BREGGETT RIDEAU (singing): I
still have learned
all you give is all you get, so
give it all

46:58.716 --> 47:00.818 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you got.

47:00.851 --> 47:07.058 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: I'm Kavitha
Cardoza of Education
Week, reporting from Keller,
Texas, for the

47:07.091 --> 47:12.930 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
"PBS NewsHour."

47:12.963 --> 47:18.769 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Colum McCann

47:18.803 --> 47:28.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Can writing be
taught, or is
it an inherent gift that some of
us have and

47:28.913 --> 47:30.681 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
others don't?

47:30.715 --> 47:34.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That is at the heart of the
National Book
Award winner Colum McCann's
newest work, the

47:34.885 --> 47:37.822 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
latest addition to the
"NewsHour" Bookshelf.

47:37.855 --> 47:42.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown talked with him at
this year's
Conference of the Association of
American

47:42.193 --> 47:45.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Writers and Writing Programs
here in Washington,
D.C.

47:45.730 --> 47:47.832 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, what is this
book, "Letters
to a Young Writer"?

47:47.865 --> 47:49.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What are you doing?

47:49.667 --> 47:52.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN, Author, "Letters
to a Young
Writer": I was asked to have an
online presence

47:52.603 --> 47:54.405 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
by my publishers.

47:54.438 --> 47:59.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I thought, well, maybe every
week I will
post a little bit of advice to a
young writer.

47:59.376 --> 48:00.444 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And it sort of took off.

48:00.478 --> 48:05.449 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I did it every week for 52
weeks last
year.

48:05.483 --> 48:08.886 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so they decided, well, we're
going to
put it out as a little book.

48:08.919 --> 48:13.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think it's the sort of
thing I would've
have liked to have gotten myself
as a younger

48:13.891 --> 48:16.794 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
writer, although I don't always
follow my
own advice.

48:16.827 --> 48:18.062 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, you teach,
right?

48:18.095 --> 48:19.530 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLUM MCCANN: I teach.

48:19.563 --> 48:21.899 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, you're used
to sort of
talking about these things.

48:21.932 --> 48:22.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLUM MCCANN: Yes.

48:22.933 --> 48:24.468 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And I love teaching.

48:24.502 --> 48:26.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there's always that debate
about whether
you can teach writing or not.

48:26.437 --> 48:28.205 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

48:28.239 --> 48:33.410 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: But I think I
teach -- I hope
I teach the virtue of fire and
stamina and

48:33.444 --> 48:35.279 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
desire and perseverance.

48:35.312 --> 48:41.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm not so sure that I can teach
people how
to, you know, write dialogue or
create plot

48:41.519 --> 48:43.287 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or anything like that.

48:43.320 --> 48:47.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But if I can get them and grab
them by the
scruff of the neck and say, you
can do this,

48:47.892 --> 48:52.363 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and if I see that fire in their
eyes, that's
when I think I know a writer.

48:52.396 --> 48:54.498 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Did you have a
reader in mind,
or...

48:54.532 --> 48:56.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: No, I suppose I
had my younger
self.

48:57.001 --> 48:58.769 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Oh, really?

48:58.803 --> 49:02.740 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: Yes, back in the
days when I
had hair and I was typing away
and getting

49:02.773 --> 49:03.841 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
all sorts of rejection letters.

49:03.874 --> 49:05.242 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: What did you say
to yourself?

49:05.276 --> 49:07.144 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: I said, you better
behave yourself.

49:07.178 --> 49:08.879 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You better learn.

49:08.913 --> 49:13.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, I talk in the book
about, like,
these romantic notions about
drinking and

49:13.117 --> 49:14.084 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
drug use.

49:14.118 --> 49:15.686 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I also talk about plot.

49:15.719 --> 49:17.321 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I talk about characterization.

49:17.354 --> 49:19.089 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I talk about empathy.

49:19.123 --> 49:22.459 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I talk about behaving yourself
and not behaving
yourself.

49:22.493 --> 49:29.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, really, I want the younger
writer to
know that she or he is
meaningful, that what

49:29.066 --> 49:32.036 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they have to say is powerful in
this world.

49:32.069 --> 49:37.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they can't come indoors,
they can't close
the curtains, they can't, like,
lock themselves

49:37.942 --> 49:39.743 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
away from the world and say
nothing.

49:39.777 --> 49:44.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Just to give
people a little
flavor of what you're doing, you
address the

49:44.348 --> 49:46.584 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
old write what you know, right?

49:46.617 --> 49:47.785 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLUM MCCANN: Right.

49:47.818 --> 49:49.787 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, you say,
don't write what
you know.

49:49.820 --> 49:51.622 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Write toward what you want to
know.

49:51.655 --> 49:52.623 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLUM MCCANN: Yes.

49:52.656 --> 49:54.024 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Now explain that.

49:54.058 --> 49:55.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: Ultimately, you
can only ever
write what you know.

49:55.626 --> 49:59.496 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It's logically and
philosophically impossible
to write what you don't know.

49:59.530 --> 50:06.070 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
However, if you sort of see
yourself writing
into a space that you don't
always recognize,

50:06.103 --> 50:11.242 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you sometimes learn things that
you knew,
but weren't entirely aware of.

50:11.275 --> 50:18.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's very liberating for a
writer to go into
a space where she or he has not
gone before,

50:18.682 --> 50:24.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because, instead of being a
tourist, you're
like an explorer now, and you're
sort of lost

50:24.722 --> 50:26.557 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in this new idea.

50:26.590 --> 50:31.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Another area,
character, knowing
your character, details that you
won't write

50:31.095 --> 50:32.062 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
about.

50:32.096 --> 50:33.297 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLUM MCCANN: Right.

50:33.330 --> 50:35.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But you know
these people so
intimately.

50:35.266 --> 50:38.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I like what you said, not just
what she had
for breakfast, but what she
wanted for breakfast.

50:38.769 --> 50:39.737 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: Right, right,
right.

50:39.770 --> 50:41.605 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Right?

50:41.639 --> 50:45.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: I call that the
little literary
slice of bacon in the morning,
not just what

50:45.075 --> 50:48.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they had, but what they really,
truly wanted
to have.

50:48.512 --> 50:52.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, if you know your character
very well,
you will know both of these
things.

50:52.750 --> 50:56.587 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: One other area I
want to -- of
the advice, structure.

50:56.620 --> 51:00.758 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You talk about the organization
of a piece
of writing and the importance of
that.

51:00.791 --> 51:02.660 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: Structure can be
really problematic.

51:02.693 --> 51:08.098 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
If you have a structure
beforehand, you're
sort of stuffing your story into
a pre-assembled

51:08.132 --> 51:09.099 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
box.

51:09.133 --> 51:10.601 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You don't want that to happen.

51:10.634 --> 51:14.371 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What you want in your writing is
to have a
sort of wildness that occurs.

51:14.405 --> 51:18.409 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then, out of the wildness, a
structure
emerges.

51:18.442 --> 51:23.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's really towards the end of
the novel that
most writers actually say, aha,
that's actually

51:23.847 --> 51:25.582 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
how I'm structuring this thing.

51:25.616 --> 51:29.787 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, you don't want to be too
aware beforehand
of what it is that you want to
say or do.

51:29.820 --> 51:32.289 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: That's
interesting, because
that sort of goes to everything
that you're

51:32.323 --> 51:33.457 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
saying in some ways, right?

51:33.490 --> 51:35.192 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLUM MCCANN: Yes.

51:35.225 --> 51:41.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So much of what I do, so much of
what we do
as writers is -- operates on the
fume of a

51:41.265 --> 51:42.232 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
gut feeling.

51:42.266 --> 51:44.134 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

51:44.168 --> 51:46.003 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: A lot of people
think that writers
are much cleverer than they
actually are.

51:46.036 --> 51:47.771 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
No, they're not.

51:47.805 --> 51:51.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they're emotionally clever,
and they go
into a character, and they feel
something

51:51.709 --> 51:54.078 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that they weren't entirely aware
of beforehand.

51:54.111 --> 51:57.014 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I know, personally, that that is
how I operate.

51:57.047 --> 52:00.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: How do you know
when you're
encountering good writing
yourself?

52:00.684 --> 52:06.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: You know because,
when you walk
outside, and you're about to be
hit by a bus,

52:06.256 --> 52:07.891 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and you get -- which I call the
bus theory.

52:07.925 --> 52:09.560 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The bus theory,
yes.

52:09.593 --> 52:13.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: And the bus misses
you, you
say thank God, because all I
wanted to do

52:13.664 --> 52:15.799 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
was finish my novel before the
bus hit me.

52:15.833 --> 52:19.136 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Listen, when I finish my novel,
the bus can
hit me all at once.

52:19.169 --> 52:22.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's when you know you're
doing something,
something relatively good.

52:22.206 --> 52:26.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: I want to go back
to this larger
question of the engagement with
the larger

52:26.210 --> 52:27.177 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
culture.

52:27.211 --> 52:28.912 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLUM MCCANN: Right.

52:28.946 --> 52:30.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Because it's been
a kind of
discussion in American writing
for a long

52:30.881 --> 52:36.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
time, right, about how engaged
writers are
or internal, too internalized at
different

52:36.854 --> 52:37.821 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
times.

52:37.855 --> 52:39.790 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLUM MCCANN: Right.

52:39.823 --> 52:40.891 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: What do you see
today in -- especially
in the younger writers that
you're dealing

52:40.924 --> 52:41.992 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
-- that you're working with?

52:42.026 --> 52:44.495 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
COLUM MCCANN: Personally, I like
the social
novel.

52:44.528 --> 52:50.034 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I like writing that gets in and
under the
hood and looks about -- at
what's going on.

52:50.067 --> 52:52.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I don't say to any writer
that that's
absolutely what they should do.

52:52.903 --> 52:57.408 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, it's like the difference
between Whitman
and Dickinson, Emily Dickinson.

52:57.441 --> 53:04.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Whitman was big and expansive
and engaged
and political and democratic and
wrote beautifully.

53:04.148 --> 53:05.949 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And Dickinson just came indoors.

53:05.983 --> 53:11.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was small and intimate and
whispering in
your ear -- both incredibly
powerful.

53:11.855 --> 53:14.358 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right,
"Letters to a Young
Writer."

